member.example:
If the header lines looks like:
from sending.com (localMachine [127.0.0.1]) by test.net (Postfix)
then the dictionary will contain two keys: "from" and "by" with the values "sending.com (localMachine [127.0.0.1])" and "test.net (Postfix)".

member.param:
 if the body should be parsed,
 if only headers should be parsed out of the  byte
array

member.summary:
Class used to contain all the task information. A task can also be added to an E-mail (
) when
the FollowUp flag is set.
